### Get all users
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users
Accept: application/json

### Get user by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1
Accept: application/json

### Get non-existent user (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/999
Accept: application/json

### Create a new user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ben",
  "email": "ben@example.com"
}

### Create user with blank name (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "bad@example.com"
}

### Update a user
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Daniel",
  "email": "dan.26@example.com"
}

### Delete a user
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/users/2
Accept: application/json

### Delete non-existent user (expect 404)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/users/999
Accept: application/json

### Create user — missing name (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "valid@example.com"
}

###

### Create user — invalid email (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Diana",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}

###

### Create user — name too short (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "A",
  "email": "diana@example.com"
}

###

### Create user — both fields invalid (expect 400, two errors)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "bad"
}

###

### Update — only name, no email (valid partial update, expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Renamed"
}

###

### Update — invalid email format (expect 400)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "email": "not-valid"
}

### Validation failure — blank name (expect 400 with field errors)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "bad-email"
}

###

### Resource not found (expect 404 with message)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/999

###

### Delete non-existent user (expect 404)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/users/999

###

### Valid create (expect 201)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Diana",
  "email": "diana@example.com"
}

###

### Valid partial update — name only (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Updated"
}

### First create a user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com"
}

###

### Create order for user 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "totalAmount": 99.99
}

###

### Create another order for user 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "totalAmount": 49.50
}

###

### Get all orders for user 1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders

###

### Get specific order
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1

###

### Update order status
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1/status?status=CONFIRMED

###

### Try wrong user id (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/999/orders/1

###

### Delete order
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/2